Sentencas: The electrochemical characteristics of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells containing pure perovskite anode of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-(delta), (LYSTA-) and composite anodes with varying fractions (30 and 50 wt%) of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ), LYSTA- (30)YSZ and LYSTA- (50)YSZ, were studied in humidified methane.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: The 8 wt% CeO2 and 4 wt% NiO, denoted as (84), were impregnated into the pure and composite anodes for efficient electrooxidation of methane.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: The studies were carried out to qualitatively estimate the kinetic parameter, exchange current density (i(o)), for methane electrooxidation.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: Evaluation in a 3-electrode configuration with an asymmetric reference electrode yielded the following activity trend: (84)LYSTA- > (84)LYSTA- (30)YSZ > (84)LYSTA- (50)YSZ in the high-overpotential region, with i(o) values of 133.2 +/- 32.5, 40.8 +/- 16.6, and 47.9 +/- 16.3 mA cm(-2) at 900 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: The presence of YSZ in the composite anodes leads to decrease in i(o) and degrading performance.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: Impedance studies clubbed with equivalent circuit modeling along with physical characterization were used to account for decreased i(o) values in composite anodes.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: Metal support interactions arising between Ni and CeO2 are studied using a high-resolution transmission electron microscope.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ

Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) studies with (84)LYSTA- anode yielded a maximum power density of 591 mW cm(-2) in hydrogen and 429 mW cm(-2) in methane.
Titulo: Kinetics of methane electrooxidation in pure and composite anodes of La0.3Y0.1Sr0.4TiO3-δ
